<item>
            <title>[AMQ-7308] Virtual Topic concurrent send with JMX consumer queue deletion can lead to kahaDb leak</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-7308</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With a fast producer on a virtual topic, a jmx op to remove a consumer queue will succeed but it is possible that an inflight send will recreate the kahadb message store and accept the message, which will never be consumed. This message will subsequently prevent cleanup/gc of kahadb leading to excessive disk usage.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
