                            <comment id="16934232" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 20 Sep 2019 09:23:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 289750d7c9849bd26f19e9116457eb72a3412d05 in activemq&apos;s branch refs/heads/master from gtully&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=activemq.git;h=289750d&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=activemq.git;h=289750d&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-7308&quot; title=&quot;Virtual Topic concurrent send with JMX consumer queue deletion can lead to kahaDb leak&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AMQ-7308&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AMQ-7308&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; - ensure kahadb message add does not auto create the message store in error, expect an existing store. fix and test&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16934240" author="gtully" created="Fri, 20 Sep 2019 09:33:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;recovery processing will recreate the message store, otherwise the expectation is that the store exists before a message add, such that an inflight send will get rejected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
